OL,3,CLisa Nandy says she's prepared to take
OL,4,Con 'cultures of silence'
OL,6,FShe said: "Having spoken with the BBC
OL,7,Fin recent weeks about the Gregg
OL,8,FWallace allegations, I am really clear
OL,9,Fthat we're seeing too many of these
OL,10,Fcultures of silence and issues being
OL,11,Fswept under the rug.
OL,13,F"People who cannot advance through the
OL,14,Fcurrent complaints system because it
OL,15,Fwould have an impact on their career,
OL,16,Fpotentially ending their career.
OL,18,F"And I am clear that people need to be
OL,19,Fheard, action has to be taken and
OL,20,Fperpetrators have to be held to
OL,21,Faccount."
